HEADWORD: Deglutinate
<hw>De*glu"ti*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Deglutinated</conjf>; <pos>p.
pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Deglutinating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>deglutinatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>deglutinare</ets> to deglutinate;
<ets>de-</ets> + <ets>glutinare</ets> to glue, <ets>gluten</ets>
glue.]</ety> <def>To loosen or separate by dissolving the glue which
unties; to unglue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deglutination</ent>⟦br⟧
